    "(3.11)To isolate its scalar contribution, we design the LagrangianL = 8 i=1 1 2 ϕ i □ϕ i -m 2 i -g 1 ϕ 1 ϕ 3 ϕ 6 -g 2 ϕ 2 ϕ 6 ϕ 7 ϕ 8 -g 3 ϕ 4 ϕ 5 ϕ 7 ϕ 8,(3.12)that precisely reproduces only this diagram to order O(g 1 g 2 g 3) in the coupling constants.",
    "(In gauge theories one might need to be a bit more careful; we can either work in a physical gauge or add up the relevant contributions that render the amplitudes gauge invariant.)",
